Spanish Stocks: Telefonica, OHL, Abertis, Acciona Shares Move

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-04-08T11:27:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/spanish-stocks-telefonica-ohl-abertis-acciona-shares-move.html
Spain’s IBEX 35 index advanced 78.3
points, or 0.7 percent, to 10,927.4 at 1:18 p.m. in Madrid. The
benchmark is heading for a 1.9 percent gain this week. The
Madrid Stock Exchange General Index rose 0.8 percent today.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Spanish market. Symbols are in parentheses after company names.  Abertis Infraestructuras SA (ABE)   fell for a first day
in three, losing 1.9 percent to 15.72 euros. The Spanish highway
operator hired AZ Capital to advise it on the sale of its Saba
Infraestructuras parking and logistics unit, Expansion reported,
citing unidentified people familiar with the matter.  Acciona SA (ANA)   gained 1.6 percent to 78.69 euros,
erasing yesterday’s loss. Spain’s second-biggest wind-farm
operator said it signed a syndicated loan for 1.42 billion euros
to refinance a loan signed in 2009 for the acquisition of
renewable energy assets from  Endesa SA. (ELE)  Endesa rose 0.8 percent
to 22.67 euros.  Ferrovial SA (FER)   increased 1.7 percent to 9.27 euros,
erasing yesterday’s drop. The Spanish manager of highways and
airports was rated “outperform” in new coverage at Exane BNP
Paribas.  Obrascon Huarte Lain SA (OHL)   climbed for a second day
in three, adding 1.6 percent to 26.73 euros. The Spanish builder
PBG SA of Poland and Spain’s Obrascon Huarte Lain SA signed a
letter of intent to work together on construction projects for
the energy industry, including pipelines and storage facilities,
in countries such as Mexico, Brazil and Russia.  Telefonica SA (TEF)   advanced for a third day this week,
gaining 1.1 percent to 18.24 euros. Spain’s Telecommunications
Market Commission increased fees for Telefonica’s unbundled
local loop to 8.32 euros from 7.79 euros, the regulator said in
an e-mailed statement today. It’s the first increase since
November 2008, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in  Madrid  at 
